cide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 1: you have used 26 of about 39 target actions so far.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "Now I can see the yellow shapes clearly:\n```\nRow 52: OOYYYYOOOOYYYYO\nRow 53: OOYYYYOOOOYYYYO\nRow 54: OOYYYYOOOOYYYYO\nRow 55: OOYYYYOOOOYYYYO\nRow 56: OOYYYYYYYYYYYYO\nRow 57: OOYYYYYYYYYYYYO\nRow 58: OOYYYYYYYYYYYYO\nRow 59: OOYYYYYYYYYYYYO\n```\nSo each yellow shape is like a \"U\" shape or a cup: two 4\u00d74 vertical bars on top with a 4\u00d712 horizontal bar at the bottom. The left bar is cols 16-19 and the right bar is cols 24-27 for yellow 1, connected by a bottom bar at rows 56-59.\nWait, but the segmentation says there are TWO yellow objects, each with 80 pixels. Let me re-examine. The ascii shows both yellow shapes in one region (cols 16-27 for yellow 1 and cols 40-51 for yellow 2). Each has the same \"U\" shape structure.\nActually wait, looking more carefully at the ascii:\n```\nRow 52: OOYYYYOOOOYYYYO\n```\nThis shows YYYY at cols 16-19, then OOOO at cols 20-23, then YYYY at cols 24-27. So there are two separate 4\u00d74 yellow blocks at the top (cols 16-19 and cols 24-27), connected by a solid bar at rows 56-59.\nBut the segmentation says there are TWO yellow objects, each with 80 pixels. Let me check if these are separate objects or connected. Looking at the boundary, it seems like each yellow shape is one connected object spanning cols 16-27 (or 40-51) with the U-shape.\nHmm wait, 80 pixels for a U-shape: top bars are 4\u00d74 = 16 each (two of them = 32), bottom bar is 4\u00d712 = 48. Total = 32 + 48 = 80. Yes, that matches!\nSo each yellow shape is a U-shape with 80 pixels. The blue rectangle is also 80 pixels (4\u00d720).\nNow, the blue rectangle is 4 rows \u00d7 20 co